#this is the something about my study of git

 	 git config file location

  ~/gitconfig

 	 make alias of a command

 git config --global alias.ci "commit -a -m"


 	modify the default editor of git

git config --global core.editor vim

add a screenshot of the project

	add the line in the README.md

	[!youimage](http://github.com/yourname/your-repository/raw/master/your-image)

	if your image is not in the root of your project,you should tell git the full root of you image

	

